  {
    "id": 63924,
    "text": "Hi All\n\nWe will be introducing a new rate-limiting configuration on the gateway. This change adds an additional, endpoint-specific hourly rate limit for the /stream/transactions endpoint.\nThe existing global rate limit of `1,550 requests per minute` across all endpoints will remain unchanged and will continue to support normal wallet usage without interruption.\nThe /stream/transactions endpoint is used by the wallet only when a user views transaction history, with subsequent requests occurring only when the user scrolls for additional records. As a result, this change is not expected to impact wallet users.\nAn hourly limit of `3,600 requests per hour` will be enforced on the `/stream/transactions` endpoint. Requests exceeding this configured rate will be throttled and blocked, while requests within the limit will continue to be allowed. This measure is intended to ensure that clients—particularly server-based integrations—appropriately pace their requests and avoid unintentional service abuse.\n\nFoundation plans to apply this change tomorrow. Please let us know any concerns immediately.",
    "date": "2026-02-23T11:51:23.000Z",
    "sender": "6848177900",
    "senderName": "Shambu",
