    "id": 63832,
    "text": "So here it is, the brand new name service. Based on legal advice, I cannot instantiate the mainnet as need to create a clear distinction between the RNS, to ensure that it's not considered a continuation, but instead a clean break. I'm obviously clear to instantiate on stokenet (as it's a testnet):\n\nPackage: package_tdx_2_1pkq94qsyttgk89fe4suh3xsq24adfeypd9s6pd0zramlt8cew4ctty\n\nComponent: component_tdx_2_1cq3hzzgwypv3494aprg76c3pvxwpxmwalm7ld257pudj8urzc6l5ap\n\nThe org for the code: https://github.com/radix-namespace\n\nMain components:\n- The scrypto for the new namespace.\n- The typescript SDK that ties into components to allow people to easily put UI's and platforms together.\n- The docs for the typescript SDK.\n- A management client that allows easy instantiation and config (reserve domains for the ecosystem) and inspection, for component verification.\n- Most of these repos contain github workflows to help out a facilitator / project leader.\n\nThis is a brand new namespace (not related to the RNS) as to ensure a clean break, both legally and to introduce new features / optimised code / flows, however, whomever instantiates can set the current .xrd as \"importable\" resources. An overview:\n\n- Register human-readable .xrd domains backed by bonded USD stablecoins.\n- Create, edit, and delete subdomains (e.g. blog.alice.xrd) under any registered domain.\n- Store arbitrary data records (wallet addresses, social links).\n- Reverse resolution (discovery) by linking an account address to a primary domain so others can look you up by address.\n- Domain import from existing NFTs / accepted domain NFT resources can prove ownership and receive the equivalent .xrd domain.\n- Third-party service providers can sign up as registrars, set a fee percentage, and earn fees on every domain registration they facilitate.\n- Bond model with rebond/unbond as domains are are backed by bonded USD stablecoins (not burned); owners can swap their bond to a different stablecoin (rebond) or return the domain to reclaim their bond (unbond).\n- Admin can pre-allocate domains to specific accounts before the system goes live; anyone can pay on behalf of the eligible claimant.\n- The admin badge is burned to go live, permanently removing all admin access and making the system fully permissionless.\n- Each domain gets its own isolated subregistry component and dApp definition account for wallet recognition.\n- Each domain NFT includes a generated QR code image stored entirely on-ledger (QR images will never dissappear / no IPFS requirements as are lightweight on-ledger SVG representations).\n- Subregistries can update their associated domain resource address, to support easy record / subdomain migration between service providers.",
    "date": "2026-02-18T22:48:20.000Z",
    "sender": "598247297",
    "senderName": "Wylie",
    "hasMedia": true,
    "mediaType": "MessageMediaWebPage",
    "replyTo": null
  },
