  {
    "id": 63435,
    "text": "Hello @stelea_RDX thanks for your getting back on this. I am happy to say the problem has now been solved by addressing 2 main issues:\n1. my payment flow which is still based on a development environment was using purely http protocol which was ok for desktop use-cases but turned out to be problematic with mobile device deep link based usage because there additional security related factors that kick in and prevents http based url connections. I have issued and installed a self-signed CA certificate and changed all usage on he client and server side based on https protocol.\n\n2. I was not enabling ‘relay’ in the RDT connectionMode which is apparently required for mobile device based deep linking usage\n\nregards",
    "date": "2025-12-26T16:15:37.000Z",
    "sender": "1233535332",
    "senderName": "oz.xrd",
    "hasMedia": false,
    "mediaType": null,
    "replyTo": 63425
  },
  {
    "id": 63428,
