  {
    "id": 63251,
    "text": "And the TypeScript library is the same 👍 The message format took me a little while, so let me share it:\n\n```\nbuilder\n   .header({\n    ...\n   })\n   .message({\n    kind: \"PlainText\",\n    value: {\n     mimeType: \"text/plain\",\n     message: {\n      kind: \"String\",\n      value: message\n     }\n    }\n   })\n   .manifest(manifest)\n   .notarize(notaryPrivateKey)```",
    "date": "2025-12-10T09:10:59.000Z",
    "sender": "1811991898",
    "senderName": "Timan | Astrolescent",
    "hasMedia": false,
    "mediaType": null,
    "replyTo": 63250
  },
  {
    "id": 63250,
    "text": "and here the answer ghenadie already gave but in more detail.\n\nThe message is part of the transaction intent: \n\npub struct IntentV1 {\n    pub header: TransactionHeaderV1,\n    pub instructions: InstructionsV1,\n    pub blobs: BlobsV1,\n    pub message: MessageV1,\n}",
    "date": "2025-12-10T07:46:18.000Z",
    "sender": "7612156674",
    "senderName": "Rockman.$ROCK.Radix",
    "hasMedia": false,
    "mediaType": null,
    "replyTo": null
  },
  {
    "id": 63249,
    "text": "Ask differently.\n\n“How can I include a message in a transaction?”\n\nThe message is part of the transaction but not of the instructions (manifest)",
