    "text": "Thanks to your guys feedback, I have fixed 2 things: the blake2b algorithm was actually using a 512 bits hash and the server was truncating the 64 byte has to 32 bytes. Now uses the correct 256 bits algorithm. Also corrected the that dAppIDAccount length to a single byte binary format 0x45. However, it is still failing signature validation?\n\n[1] ============================================================\n[1] ✓ Server ready - Badge whitelist + ROLA authentication active\n[1] ============================================================\n[1] [REQUEST] GET /db/merchants\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] Signed Challenge Object: {\n[1]   type: 'account',\n[1]   challenge: '38aef7f9354e4cbbaa93aa35e48f04530de6ecaaf97316a42e88025ac7a649ae',\n[1]   proof: {\n[1]     publicKey: '0116cdf4eb55eb071da45725718cec4962d75720e5a4b0a409d5971a287a3bc4',\n[1]     signature: '556e540c83d870701b5fe5c83796a4b75306ca2e7f19d8e52cea9c5bca1042daa0da434d4ac19fbb3909881ce5853d4980020de7a873e3fe742e300189c75b06',\n[1]     curve: 'curve25519'\n[1]   },\n[1]   address: 'account_tdx_2_12y85k44mq77eqhnzst0r0r4qtg37gnqu4h7dw8a4k8lajaf0yk4uay'\n[1] }\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] Verification request for: account_tdx_2_12y85k...\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] Challenge (client-generated): 38aef7f9354e4cbbaa93aa35e48f04530de6ecaaf97316a42e88025ac7a649ae\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] Public Key: 0116cdf4eb55eb071da45725718cec4962d75720e5a4b0a409d5971a287a3bc4\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] Signature: 556e540c83d870701b5fe5c83796a4b75306ca2e7f19d8e52cea9c5bca1042daa0da434d4ac19fbb3909881ce5853d4980020de7a873e3fe742e300189c75b06\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] Curve: curve25519\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] dApp Definition: account_tdx_2_128n7smvlgf0hudm5p5a67m9taru30nz3xqxn6sf7sxtzh00swkyn6l\n[1] [ROLA-SIMPLE] Origin: http://localhost:5173\n[1] [ROLA-SIG-DEBUG] ========== SIGNATURE VERIFICATION DETAILS ==========\n[1] [ROLA-SIG-DEBUG] Challenge: 38aef7f9354e4cbbaa93aa35e48f04530de6ecaaf97316a42e88025ac7a649ae\n[1] [ROLA-SIG-DEBUG] Public Key: 0116cdf4eb55eb071da45725718