  {
    "id": 62897,
    "text": "Algorithm Name Confusion: \"BLAKE2B-SHA256\" suggests they might be chaining two hash functions, which is incorrect for ROLA.\nThe correct ROLA flow should be:\nConstruct message: R + challenge (32 bytes binary) + dAppIdLength (ASCII) + dAppIdAddress + origin\nHash with BLAKE2b-256 (single hash, 32-byte output)\nVerify signature with Ed25519 using the cleaned public key (without 01 prefix)",
    "date": "2025-11-11T19:44:31.000Z",
    "sender": "316385590",
    "senderName": "avaunt > ShardSpace | Notix | Atomix | Bullring",
    "hasMedia": false,
    "mediaType": null,
    "replyTo": null
  },
  {
    "id": 62896,
    "text": "Claude is telling me\n\n\"The message construction looks correct (125 bytes matching on both sides), and the public key handling seems right (removing the 01 prefix), so the hash algorithm is the most likely culprit.\nRecommendation: Check which BLAKE2b library is being used and ensure it's configured for 256-bit output (32 bytes), not 512-bit, and that no additional SHA256 is being applied.\"\n\n\n```// Ensure using BLAKE2b-256, not BLAKE2b-512 or SHA256\nimport { blake2b } from 'some-crypto-library';\n\n// Hash should be exactly BLAKE2b with 32-byte output\nconst messageHash = blake2b(messageBuffer, null, 32); // 32 bytes output\n\n// Then verify with Ed25519\nconst isValid = ed25519.verify(signature, messageHash, publicKeyWithoutPrefix);```",
    "date": "2025-11-11T19:43:36.000Z",
    "sender": "316385590",
    "senderName": "avaunt > ShardSpace | Notix | Atomix | Bullring",
    "hasMedia": false,
    "mediaType": null,
    "replyTo": null
  },
