    "text": "My dApp’s ROLA Challenge Based User Authentication is failing presumably because the steps being executed by my backend server is not matching the cryptographic operations being executed by the Wallet.\n\nI would be most obliged if anyone can help to identify where I am going wrong on this. \n\nMany Thanks\n\nThe details below provides the current operations of the dApp which comprises of the client component and the associated backend server.\n\nThe cryptographic operations being executed by the dApp Server are as follows:\n\n1. Construct SAME ROLA message (125 bytes binary)\n messageBuffer = construct(\"R\" + challenge_bytes + ...)\n\n2. Hash with BLAKE2B-SHA256\n messageHash = BLAKE2B(messageBuffer) → 32 bytes\n\n3. Remove public key prefix\n cleanKey = remove \"01\" from publicKey\n\n4. Verify signature with Ed25519\n isValid = Ed25519.verify(\n messageHash, // 32 bytes\n signature, // 64 bytes (as hex string)\n cleanKey // 32 bytes (as hex string)\n     )\n\nI have attached debug logs from my dApp to provide more insight into this problem.",
