ly is only released when the the circulating supply of a meme token drops below x percent of the historical maximum, and stays below that threshold for a week.\n\n**Guaranteed Eventual payout:** To ensure that the jackpot is triggered at some point, the threshold will have to increase to account for lost wallets. It could start at 0.1 percent and rise by 1 percentage point per year. This way, people know for sure that they will get a share of the jackpot if they are able to wait long enough.\n\n**A League of Degens:** By standardizing this protocol, we enable a Meme Token Arms Race on Radix. Projects can compete fiercely on:\n\n**Fee Settings:** (3%/3% 5%/5%, or dynamic curves)\n**Jackpot Thresholds:** (Aggressive 1% vs. Hyper-Degen 0.1%)\n**Viral Narratives:** (Dog, Cat, Frog, or Radix-native memes)📈 \n\n**Why This Will Put Radix on the Map:**\n**Magnet for Liquidity:** The combination of passive XRD dividends and the massive jackpot creates a positive Expected Value (+EV) scenario for the most aggressive traders and speculators. This guaranteed degen energy is what drives billions in trading volume on other chains.\n**Viral Competition = Explosive Growth:** Instead of waiting for one project to succeed, we launch an entire fleet of tokens powered by JDP. The one that gains the most traction will attract global attention, driving new users and TVL (Total Value Locked) to Radix overnight.\n**The Bridge to Serious Projects:** The massive volume, user adoption, and liquidity generated by a viral JDP meme token will establish Radix as a proven, high-throughput platform. First, we attract the degens for the volume. Then, we use that volume and proven scalability to attract the serious Real-World Asset (RWA) and institutional projects. \n\nLet's stop waiting for the market. Let's build the viral mechanism that forces the market to look at Radix.\n\nAnd now. Good bye from me. You have what is needed to have a great marketing tool for Radix. attract degen energy to put Radix on the map to eventually attract more serious stuff on radix. A single whale could make this happen.\n\nI personally like the name \"The 401k Club\" for one of those meme tokens.",
