    "text": "No, not aware of. If it is working without errors you are good and can just continue that way. Often also newer Rust versions work, there are just sometimes incompatibilies which come up and break either the build itself or sometimes just break running the scrypto tests locally. But if it works you are good. Most important is probably setting base64ct to 1.6.0 and using Cmake  < 4.0",
