  {
    "id": 62756,
    "text": "This jackpot token idea that I have been writing about. If it was created just once by someone and open sourced, it could be something that new meme tokens could easily implement with different settings, and we could have a bunch of token sinks removing tokens from circulating supply potentially for years or a decade.\nExample\nMeme token with 6 percent tax\n3 percent going to dividend pool where every holder gets dividends when other people are trading.\n3 percent going to jackpot pool which will be triggered when number of circulating tokens outside the liquidity pool goes below x percent of the historical maximum where people then have maybe a month to sell their tokens to claim their share of the jackpot. Or they could choose not to sell and keep their tokens for round 2.\n\nI am not good enough at Scrypto to create it, and I don't think people would buy anything created by me, but I think it could be good for Radix to have this, and I have thought a lot about how to implement it. I spent a bunch of time with Grok looking at potential problems and solutions for those problems. If any programmer agrees that it could be good to have these token sinks on Radix to reduce circulating supply for some time and thereby increasing scarcity, I can help with ideas for implementation.\n\nThere have been some comments about stuff like this being a lottery, but really it is a game of patience. A transfer of wealth from the impatient to the patient. There is a guaranteed payout if people are patient enough and a guaranteed profit if they are smart enough not to buy at too high a price compared to the size of the jackpot, because there could be some +EV situations where it would be cheaper to buy tokens than what people would get from the jackpot being triggered.\n\nI said 6 percent tax but different meme tokens could use different percentages and different thresholds for triggering the jackpot, and eventually there might be a clear winner with great meme power, lots of trading and a huge jackpot. I am confident that this would be a net positive for Radix. It would be unique, and there would be something for people to be excited about.\n\nI personally have this idea of a meme token called the 401k club where people can create multiple different characters which are all part of the 401k club. Every big dip in price could be celebrated as just one of our members getting an early retirement :-)\n\nThe ultimate goal would be to make the jackpot pool big enough that it can no longer be ignored by Solana degens, who would sell their SOL for XRD just to buy a meme token on Radix. I hope that someone will consider this even though the idea is coming from someone who is definitely not popular in this community.",
